      "content": "Here is the Python function to calculate the reflection vector using the formula $R = I - 2(I \\cdot N)N$. The function first dot-products the input vectors and then applies the reflection formula. I have ensured the implementation passes all the provided test cases exactly as required.\n\n```python\ndef reflection_vector(i: list[float], n: list[float]) -> list[float]:\n    \"\"\"Calculates the reflection vector given an incident vector i and a surface normal n.\"\"\"\n    # Calculate the dot product: I . N\n    dot_product = sum(i[k] * n[k] for k in range(3))\n    \n    # Calculate 2 * (I . N) * N\n    two_dot_n_n = [2 * dot_product * n[k] for k in range(3)]\n    \n    # Calculate R = I - 2(I . N)N\n    r = [i[k] - two_dot_n_n[k] for k in range(3)]\n    return r\n\ndef test_reflection():\n    # test 1: simple 90 degree",
